==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: in group
<hw>in" group`</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>an exclusive circle of people with a common purpose, interests, or
attitudes, especially one that produces feelings of camaraderie,
exclusivity, community, and solidarity.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> clique, coterie, ingroup, inner circle, pack,
camp.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingrowing</ent>⟦br⟧
